{"actor":"Jørgen Gundersen","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-04T07:58:29Z","event_type":"claimed","id":26,"issue_id":"devenv-71n","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"Jørgen Gundersen\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"devenv-71n\",\"title\":\"Bug: allocate_port calls bare python3 which is not installed\",\"description\":\"bin/devenv:167-172 — allocate_port() calls bare 'python3' but python3 is not installed in the devenv container. The function always returns 1, causing SSH port allocation to silently fail and fall through to die. Project convention is to use 'uv run python3' for anything Python-related. Recommended fix: rewrite to use 'uv run python3 -c ...' per research Open Decision #6.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"jg@gundersenj.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:04:39Z\",\"created_by\":\"Jørgen Gundersen\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-03T11:04:39Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Jørgen Gundersen","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-04T07:59:03Z","event_type":"closed","id":27,"issue_id":"devenv-71n","new_value":"Fixed: replaced bare python3 with uv run python3 in allocate_port(); shellcheck clean; committed f4556c8","old_value":""}
